From: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Oct 2010 12:25:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 178/233] fsl/pamu: don't reconfigure the pamu in dump kernel

We don't stop the pamu in panic kernel. That mean the pamu is
still running when the dump kernel boot. So don't reconfigure
it.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/sysdev/fsl_pamu.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/sysdev/fsl_pamu.c b/arch/powerpc/sysdev/fsl_pamu.c
index dcd0ed2..f905169 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/sysdev/fsl_pamu.c
+++ b/arch/powerpc/sysdev/fsl_pamu.c
@@ -479,4 +479,6 @@ static __init int fsl_of_pamu_init(void)
 	return of_register_platform_driver(&fsl_of_pamu_driver);
 }
 
+#ifndef CONFIG_CRASH_DUMP
 arch_initcall(fsl_of_pamu_init);
+#endif
